title: PPPP Zia Abbas Shah wins PS-58 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan People’s Party Parliamentarians’ (PPPP) Syed Zia Abbas Shah has won the Sindh Assembly election from PS-58, Tando Allahyar-I by securing 57,217 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Rahila Magsi of the Grand Democratic Alliance, who bagged votes 42,587.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 48.47 %.
